'''熱設計功耗'''（{{lang-en|'''T'''hermal '''D'''esign '''P'''ower}}，縮寫{{lang|en|'''TDP'''}}，又譯'''散熱設計功率'''<ref name="散熱設計功率">{{Cite web |url = https://www.intel.com.au/content/www/au/en/support/articles/000055611/processors.html |title = Intel®處理器中的散熱設計功率（TDP） |author = 000055611 |date = 2019-11-20 |publisher = Intel |language = en |accessdate = 2020-03-29 |quote = TDP stands for Thermal Design Power, in watts, and refers to the power consumption under the maximum theoretical load.  Power consumption is less than TDP under lower loads. The TDP is the maximum power that one should be designing the system for. This ensures operation to published specs under the maximum theoretical workload. |archive-date = 2021-03-18 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210318145946/https://www.intel.com.au/content/www/au/en/support/articles/000055611/processors.html |dead-url = no }}</ref>）是指[[處理器|處理器]]在运行實際[[應用程式|應用程式]]時，可產生的最大[[熱量|熱量]]<ref name="熱設計電源是否意味著真正的功耗">{{Cite web |url = https://www.intel.com.tr/content/www/tr/tr/support/articles/000031072/processors/intel-core-processors.html |title = 熱設計電源是否意味著真正的功耗？ |author = 000031072 |date = 2019-04-11 |publisher = Intel |language = en |accessdate = 2020-03-29 |quote = Thermal Design Power (TDP) is the maximum amount of heat that a processor can produce when running real life applications. It is used mostly to match up processors with an adequate heat sink that is capable of cooling down that processor effectively. |archive-date = 2021-03-18 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210318145917/https://www.intel.com.tr/content/www/tr/tr/support/articles/000031072/processors/intel-core-processors.html |dead-url = no }}</ref>。TDP主要用於和處理器相匹配時，散熱器能夠有效地[[冷卻|冷卻]]處理器的依據<ref name="熱設計電源是否意味著真正的功耗" />。

== 概論 ==
TDP通常作為-{zh-hans:台式; zh-hant:桌上型}-、[[筆記本電腦|筆記本電腦]]散熱系統設計、大型電腦散熱設計等散熱／降耗設計的重要參考指-{}-標。TDP越大，表明[[CPU|CPU]]在工作時會產生的單位時間[[熱量|熱量]]越大。對於散熱系統來說，需要將TDP作為散熱能力設計的最低標準，也就是散熱系統至少要能散出TDP數值所表示的單位時間熱量。例如，一個[[筆記本電腦|筆記型電腦]]的中央處理器TDP被標示為20W，這代表它必須搭配至少20W熱功率的消散方式（通過主動式散熱手段如使用[[風扇|風扇]]，或是被動式散熱手段如[[熱管|熱管]]散熱）而不超出晶片的最大[[結溫|結溫]]。

== TDP與CPU功耗 ==
=== 定義 ===
测量TDP时需要保证[[CPU|CPU]]所有核心全速运行、最大化测试温度（一般是Tj 105°C，CPU芯片温度）、包括核心电压（VDD）、NB电压（VDDNB）、IO电压（VDDIO）、VLDT、VDDA等在内的电路电压最大化<ref name="SDP 2">{{Cite web |url = https://www.expreview.com/23334-2.html |title = SDP到底是什么？ |author = bolvar |date = 2013-01-17 |publisher = 超能網 |language = zh-cn |accessdate = 2020-03-29 |quote = TDP（Thermal Design Power，热设计功耗）这个单词在超能的新闻和评测里也见了太多了，它是指处理器达到最高负荷的时候释放出的热量，单位为瓦（W），这是维基百科里的解释，Intel的官方定义中说法类似，也是指CPU在最极端情况下的热量散发情况。 |archive-date = 2020-03-29 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200329082011/https://www.expreview.com/23334-2.html |dead-url = no }}</ref>。95W的TDP意味着CPU散热器要能在1秒内将95[[焦耳|焦耳]]的热量散发出去，这样CPU就不会因为散热不及时导致热量积累进而烧坏CPU<ref name="SDP 2" />。

